    <h1>Types and Functions</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Bartosz Milewski &middot; 2014 &middot; <a href="https://bartoszmilewski.com/2014/11/24/types-and-functions/">Category Theory for Programmers, Ch. 2</a></p>

    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">Prereqs: <a href="/reading/category-theory/milewski-01/">🍞 Chapter 1 (Category)</a>. 5 min.</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Types are <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Set_(mathematics)"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>sets</a>. Functions are morphisms between them. The category <strong>Hask</strong> has Haskell types as objects and pure functions as arrows. Every type is extended with <strong>bottom</strong> (&perp;), the value representing non-termination.</p>
    </div>

